Key Entities (11 Main Tables):
Core Academic Entities:

STUDENTS - Student personal information and academic details
INSTRUCTORS - Faculty information
COURSES - Course catalog
COURSE_SECTIONS - Specific course offerings per semester
DEPARTMENTS - Academic departments/colleges

Scheduling & Registration:

SEMESTERS - Academic terms
TIME_SLOTS - Class meeting times
ENROLLMENTS - Student course registrations

Business Rules:

COURSE_PREREQUISITES - Prerequisite requirements
RETAKE_REQUESTS - Retake approval workflow

System Management:

USERS - Authentication and authorization
ENROLLMENT_STATUS - Lookup table for enrollment states

Key Relationships Shown:

Students ↔ Enrollments ↔ Course Sections (Many-to-Many through Enrollments)
Courses ↔ Course Prerequisites (Self-referencing for prerequisite chains)
Instructors ↔ Course Sections (One instructor per section)
Departments ↔ Students/Instructors/Courses (All belong to departments)
Course Sections ↔ Time Slots (One section can have multiple time slots)
